1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,864
Galatians 1. Paul, an apostle, (not of men, neither by man, but by Jesus Christ, and God the Father, who raised him from

2
00:00:09,864 --> 00:00:12,192
the dead;)

3
00:00:12,192 --> 00:00:19,464
And all the brethren which are with me, unto the churches of Galatia: Grace be to you and peace from God the Father, and

4
00:00:19,464 --> 00:00:26,471
from our Lord Jesus Christ, Who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us from this present evil world,

5
00:00:26,471 --> 00:00:32,832
according to the will of God and our Father: To whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.

6
00:00:32,832 --> 00:00:39,672
I marvel that ye are so soon removed from him that called you into the grace of Christ unto another gospel: Which is not

7
00:00:39,672 --> 00:00:44,687
another; but there be some that trouble you, and would pervert the gospel of Christ.

8
00:00:44,687 --> 00:00:51,527
But though we, or an angel from heaven, preach any other gospel unto you than that which we have preached unto you, let

9
00:00:51,527 --> 00:00:53,591
him be accursed.

10
00:00:53,591 --> 00:01:01,295
As we said before, so say I now again, If any man preach any other gospel unto you than that ye have received, let him

11
00:01:01,295 --> 00:01:08,448
be accursed. For do I now persuade men, or God? or do I seek to please men?

12
00:01:08,448 --> 00:01:12,768
for if I yet pleased men, I should not be the servant of Christ.

13
00:01:12,768 --> 00:01:18,552
But I certify you, brethren, that the gospel which was preached of me is not after man.

14
00:01:18,552 --> 00:01:24,648
For I neither received it of man, neither was I taught it, but by the revelation of Jesus Christ.

15
00:01:24,648 --> 00:01:31,824
For ye have heard of my conversation in time past in the Jews’ religion, how that beyond measure I persecuted the church

16
00:01:31,824 --> 00:01:39,072
of God, and wasted it: And profited in the Jews’ religion above many my equals in mine own nation, being more

17
00:01:39,072 --> 00:01:42,744
exceedingly zealous of the traditions of my fathers.

18
00:01:42,744 --> 00:01:49,992
But when it pleased God, who separated me from my mother’s womb, and called me by his grace, To reveal his Son in me,

19
00:01:49,992 --> 00:01:56,880
that I might preach him among the heathen; immediately I conferred not with flesh and blood: Neither went I up to

20
00:01:56,880 --> 00:02:03,672
Jerusalem to them which were apostles before me; but I went into Arabia, and returned again unto Damascus.

21
00:02:03,672 --> 00:02:09,960
Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to see Peter, and abode with him fifteen days.

22
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:14,448
But other of the apostles saw I none, save James the Lord’s brother.

23
00:02:14,448 --> 00:02:19,776
Now the things which I write unto you, behold, before God, I lie not.

24
00:02:19,776 --> 00:02:27,144
Afterwards I came into the regions of Syria and Cilicia; And was unknown by face unto the churches of Judaea which were

25
00:02:27,144 --> 00:02:28,896
in Christ:

26
00:02:28,896 --> 00:02:35,496
But they had heard only, That he which persecuted us in times past now preacheth the faith which once he destroyed.

27
00:02:35,496 --> 00:02:37,968
And they glorified God in me.

